section.section:
Notwithstanding any other law, the governing body of a political subdivision may transfer jurisdiction over, lease, lend, give, sell, or convey to an authority, on the request of the authority, with or without consideration, any of the following:
Any facility;
Any right or interest in a facility;
Any property that appertains to a facility;
Any real property; or
Any right or interest in real property.
